    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 30 May 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He is not getting any letters from Oláh these days,
                            although there is someone to take the letters, he thinks this must be
                            due to Oláh’s nonchalance. They have received a letter from Rome,
                            according to which the Pope has appointed six new Cardinals, including
                            John Fisher, whom King Henry VIII is holding in jail. The rest, except
                            for Caspare Contareno, who is above reproach, does not differ from the
                            usual congregation of Cardinals. He voted for the Lutheran bishop from
                            Paris to favor the French, he knows the rest. The imperial fleet
                            consists of 330 boats, and Lucretia Caballis will tell him about the
                            Turkish affairs. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Iam aliquot dies sunt, ex quo nullas tuas litteras accepimus, quod
                    puto negligentia tua factum esse. Nam tu, qui in otio es, quid est, quod omnes
                    ferme tabellarios ab hinc duos menses ad nos venientes praeteristi sine litteris
                    tuis. Noli, amabo, Olae Carissime, hac mecum taciturnitate uti, et de rebus
                    vestris fac me et de statu rerum tuarum frequenter certiorem. Ex litteris
                    Urbanis intelleximus <persName>pontificem</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.1">Pope Paul III.</note> VI cardinales designasse,<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.2">In the second Consistory for the promotion of
                        cardinals, Pope Paul III created seven cardinals: Nicolaus Schönberg,
                        Hieronymus de Ginutiis, Jacobus Simoneta, Johannes Fisher, Johannes de
                        Bellayo, Gasparus Contarenus and Marinus Ascanius de Carraciolis. See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Van Gulik–Eubel</hi> 1923, 23–24; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">De Vocht</hi> 1961, 241.</note> inter quos habetis
                        <persName>episcopum Ruffensem</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.3"
                        >John Fisher.</note> quem <persName>rex Anglus</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">King Henry VIII.</note><choice>
                        <orig>vir sane bonus et intelligens</orig>
                        <supplied>virum sane bonum et intelligentem</supplied>
                    </choice> in carceribus habet.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.5">He was
                        executed not much later, on 22 June, 1535, at the order of King Henry
                        VIII.</note> Reliqui, excepto <persName>Contareno patricio
                        Veneto</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Caspare Contareno or
                        Gasparo Contarini (†1542) was Apostolic Legat and Cardinal, and he wrote the
                        book <hi rend="italic">De magistratibus et republica Venetorum libri
                            quinque</hi> (Veneto, 1551), see <hi rend="smallcap">De Vocht</hi> 1961,
                        241, 267–268.</note> philosopho et theologo, vitae integritate cum paucis
                    conferendo, ab consueto cardinalium coetu non degenerant. In Gallorum gratia
                    elegit <persName>episcopum Parisiensem</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.7">Jean du Bellay (1492–1560) was Bishop of Paris from
                        1532.</note> Lutheranum, cetera nosti. Classis caesaris CCCXXX navium erit,
                    apparatus ingens. Res Turcicas intelliges de <persName>Lucretia</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.8">Lucretia Caballis (vom Ross).</note> nostra.
                    Tu vale et <persName>Sceppero</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.9"
                        >Cornelis de Schepper.</note> nostro me commenda. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XXX. Maii MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
